Table 1.9. Relation of Gross Domestic Product, Gross National Product, 
Net National Product, National Income, and Personal Income
[Billions of dollars]
Bureau of Economic Analysis
Downloaded on 6/24/02 At 5:49:40 PM    Published date is 5/28/2002
0, Year
1,Gross domestic product
2,Plus: Income receipts from the rest of the world
3,Less: Income payments to the rest of the world
4,Equals: Gross national product
5,Less: Consumption of fixed capital
6,        Private
7,          Capital consumption allowances
8,          Less: Capital consumption adjustment
9,        Government
10,          General government
11,          Government enterprises
12,Equals: Net national product
13,Less: Indirect business tax and nontax liability
14,      Business transfer payments
15,      Statistical discrepancy
16,Plus: Subsidies less current surplus of government enterprises
17,Equals: National income
18,Less: Corporate profits with inventory valuation and capital consumption adjustments
19,      Net interest
20,      Contributions for social insurance
21,      Wage accruals less disbursements
22,Plus: Personal interest income
23,      Personal dividend income
24,      Government transfer payments to persons
25,      Business transfer payments to persons
26,Equals: Personal income
27,  Gross domestic income
28,  Gross national income
29,  Net domestic product
